  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat</strong> the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7 and season the chicken with the chilli flakes (can&rsquo;t handle the heat? Go easy!) and a generous pinch of salt</p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat</strong> a large, wide-based pan (with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> vegetable oil</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once </strong>hot, cook the chicken for 2 min or until golden brown</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, slice the pak choi in half, lengthways</p>\r\n<p><strong>Transfer </strong>the golden chicken to a baking tray (use tin foil to avoid mess!) and put it in the&nbsp;oven for 12-15 min&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Return</strong>&nbsp;the pan to a high heat and once hot, add the pak choi, cut-side down and cook for 2-3 min or until charred&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> done, transfer the pak choi to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the rice, 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> water and a pinch of salt to a pot with a lid over a high heat and bring to the boil</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, dice the plums&nbsp;finely, discarding the stones</p>\r\n<p><strong>Return</strong>&nbsp;the pan to a medium-low heat and once hot, add the plums with 100ml<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;[200ml]</span>&nbsp;water</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cook</strong>&nbsp;for 2-4 min</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add&nbsp;</strong>the hoisin, soy sauce, sesame seeds and&nbsp;1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span>&nbsp;sugar and cook for 1-2 min&nbsp;or until the sauce has a thin jam-like consistency</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong>&nbsp;done, remove from the heat and stir in half the toasted sesame oil - this is your hoisin plum sauce</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/596.-step--5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Remove </strong>the chicken thighs from the oven and push them to one side of the tray</p>\r\n<p><strong>Spoon</strong> a little&nbsp;of the hoisin-plum sauce over each chicken thigh, add the pak choi to the same tray and return the tray to the oven for a final 5 min</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
